<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-491-181  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 491 181.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Oct 8 1990 v4 n36 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CIA develops instruments for language training. (CentralIntelligence Agency)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Richardson, Jennifer.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The CIA has developed a computerized multimedia languageproficiency program, called Exito, which is now one of twointeractive video programs being used at the agency's LanguageTraining Division (LTD).andP;  Exito is a multimedia languageproficiency program used to help in the training and evaluation ofCIA officers.andP;  The Exito program is being ported for Macintoshcomputers and IBM PS/2s by CIA computer and language experts.andP;  TheCIA hopes that the program will catch on in government as well asprivate agencies.andP;  The Testing Oral Proficiency (TOPS) program isthe other interactive video program used by the CIA.andP;  TOPS teststhe language skills of the CIA's case officers and allows studentsto interact at terminals with audio and video-recorded nativespeakers working through hypothetical, every-day situations insome foreign country.andP;  The CIA is working on Russian and Arabicversions of TOPS.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Language TranslationMultimedia TechnologyInteractive VideoInteractive SystemsSoftwareApplicationsUnited States. Central Intelligence AgencyTraining of Employees.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>